<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A lot of stuff happens in crypto markets that,=
 if it happened in the stock market, would obviously be securities fraud. T=
here is insider trading in crypto tokens. There is market manipulation. The=
re are pump-and-dumps. All the standard illegal stuff that happens in stock=
 markets also happens in crypto markets.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a fairly popular view=C2=A0in crypto =
that it is not illegal when it happens in crypto, that crypto markets are g=
overned by their own rules, that =E2=80=9Ccode is law,=E2=80=9D that if you=
 do a thing that is not explicitly forbidden by the terms of the crypto pla=
tform you are using then no government should have any authority to stop yo=
u. This is not the=C2=A0<em>only=C2=A0</em>view in crypto =E2=80=94=C2=A0a =
lot of people disagree =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it is=C2=A0<em>a=C2=A0</em>view. =
It is not, I think it is safe to say, the view of US federal prosecutors. T=
heir view is that this stuff is all just as illegal in crypto markets as it=
 is in the stock market, that it is fraud,=C2=A0and that if it catches thei=
r attention they can and will bring criminal cases. And so <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30334334.286518/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDYtMDIvZG9uLXQtaW5zaWRlci10c=
mFkZS1uZnRzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMjMyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRt=
X3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDEyMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHV=
mZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB31b34634" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  they do</a>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This seems pretty simple for federal prosecuto=
rs at the US Department of Justice. But it is harder for the US Securities =
and Exchange Commission, because the SEC can regulate only securities, and =
there is disagreement about which crypto tokens are =E2=80=9Csecurities.=E2=
=80=9D On the one hand, the SEC=C2=A0<em>really=C2=A0</em>wants to bring th=
ese cases:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It wants to be the regulator in charge=
 of crypto, and cracking down on manipulation and fraud is a key aspect of =
that.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">These cases =E2=80=94=C2=A0m=
arket manipulation, insider trading, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0tend to be easy ca=
ses to win, since the people did bad stuff. If the SEC brings cases against=
 crypto lending platforms, arguing that they are doing unregistered securit=
ies offerings, those lending platforms will hire good lawyers and tell a sy=
mpathetic story about how they are trying to offer a good product that peop=
le want; a judge might rule that their offering was not a security. (It is =
easier for the SEC if the lending platform has <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30334334.286518/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLm=
NvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDEtMTcvc2VjLWNvbWVzLWZvci1nZW1pbmktdG9vL=
WxhdGU_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEyMzIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291=
cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMTIzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9e065aea" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  already lost its customers=E2=80=
=99 money</a>!)=C2=A0If it brings a case=C2=A0against a crypto insider trad=
er, a judge won=E2=80=99t want to throw out the case because=C2=A0<em>the i=
nsider trader seems bad</em>, so the judge will be=C2=A0more inclined to ru=
le that the relevant token was a security.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-botto=
m: 5px;">Thus, by going after the worst cases in crypto, the SEC can expand=
 its jurisdiction without too much objection.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, these cases are awkward:</p=
>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The SEC does have to prove not only th=
e bad conduct (manipulation, insider trading, etc.) and bad intent, but als=
o that the underlying thing was a security. Federal prosecutors don=E2=80=
=99t have that problem; they can just argue that the conduct was wire fraud=
.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If the underlying thing was a se=
curity, then=C2=A0<em>probably=C2=A0</em>it was offered illegally. If you b=
ought some crypto token and pumped up the price and then sold it and the SE=
C sues you for market manipulation, you can say =E2=80=9Cwell it wasn=E2=80=
=99t a security,=E2=80=9D and the SEC can say =E2=80=9Cyes it was,=E2=80=9D=
 and you can say =E2=80=9Cwell the people who issued the security didn=E2=
=80=99t register it with the SEC and offer it legally,=E2=80=9D and the SEC=
 can say =E2=80=9Cdoesn=E2=80=99t matter, you still can=E2=80=99t manipulat=
e it,=E2=80=9D and you can say things like =E2=80=9Cwell then I was defraud=
ed too, since I bought it from them,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cwhy are you going=
 after me and not them?=E2=80=9D</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/30334334.286518/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW=
9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMTIvZGVmaS1kaXNjb3ZlcnMtbmV3LW1hcmtldC1tYW5pcHVsY=
XRpb25zP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMjMyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3Nv=
dXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDEyMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBea39fe74" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked</a> in <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30334334.286518/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMjAvbWFraW5nLWNyeXB0by1oY=
WNraW5nLWxlc3MtbHVjcmF0aXZlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMjMyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRp=
